TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization.AuthorizeRouteView
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
             Combines the behaviors of <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization.AuthorizeView" /> and <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.RouteView" />,
             so that it displays the page matching the specified route but only if the user
             is authorized to see it.
            
             Additionally, this component supplies a cascading parameter of type <see cref="T:System.Threading.Tasks.Task`1" />,
             which makes the user's current authentication state available to descendants.
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: NotAuthorized
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The content that will be displayed if the user is not authorized.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Authorizing
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The content that will be displayed while asynchronous authorization is in progress.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Resource
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The resource to which access is being controlled.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RouteData
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the route data. This determines the page that will be
            displayed and the parameter values that will be supplied to the page.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DefaultLayout
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the type of a layout to be used if the page does not
            declare any layout. If specified, the type must implement <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.IComponent" />
            and accept a parameter named <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.LayoutComponentBase.Body" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Context
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the parameter name for all child content expressions.

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValidationDelay
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Validation debounce delay in milliseconds. This can help improve rendering performance of forms with real-time validation of inputs
            i.e. when textfields have Immediate="true"
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SuppressRenderingOnValidation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When true, the form will not re-render its child contents on validation updates (i.e. when IsValid changes).
            This is an optimization which can be necessary especially for larger forms on older devices.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SuppressImplicitSubmission
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When true, will not cause a page refresh on Enter if any input has focus.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            https://www.w3.org/TR/2018/SPSD-html5-20180327/forms.html#implicit-submission
            Usually this is not wanted, as it can cause a page refresh in the middle of editing a form. 
            When the form is in a dialog this will cause the dialog to close. So by default we suppress it.
            </remarks>

            <para>Func<T, IEnumerable< string >> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>

            <para>Func<T, Task< string >> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>

BoundAttributes.Name: T
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the type of the type parameter T for the MudBlazor.MudTable<T> component.

BoundAttributes.Name: RowTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines how a table row looks like. Use MudTd to define the table cells and their content.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildRowContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Row Child content of the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowEditingTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines how a table row looks like in edit mode (for selected row). Use MudTd to define the table cells and their content.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HorizontalScrollbar
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines if the table has a horizontal scrollbar.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Items
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data to display in the table. MudTable will render one row per item
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Filter
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A function that returns whether or not an item should be displayed in the table. You can use this to implement your own search function.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnRowClick
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Button click event.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowClassFunc
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Returns the class that will get joined with RowClass. Takes the current item and row index.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowStyleFunc
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Returns the style that will get joined with RowStyle. Takes the current item and row index.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItem
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Returns the item which was last clicked on in single selection mode (that is, if MultiSelection is false)
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItemChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Callback is called when a row has been clicked and returns the selected item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItems
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If MultiSelection is true, this returns the currently selected items. You can bind this property and the initial content of the HashSet you bind it to will cause these rows to be selected initially.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItemsChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Callback is called whenever items are selected or deselected in multi selection mode.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ServerData
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Supply an async function which (re)loads filtered, paginated and sorted data from server.
            Table will await this func and update based on the returned TableData.
            Used only with ServerData
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Elevation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The higher the number, the heavier the drop-shadow. 0 for no shadow.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Square
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set true to disable rounded corners
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Outlined
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true, table will be outlined.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Bordered
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true, table's cells will have left/right borders.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Dense
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set true for rows with a narrow height
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Hover
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set true to see rows hover on mouse-over.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Striped
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true, striped table rows will be used.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Breakpoint
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            At what breakpoint the table should switch to mobile layout. Takes None, Xs, Sm, Md, Lg and Xl the default behavior is breaking on Xs.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FixedHeader
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When true, the header will stay in place when the table is scrolled. Note: set Height to make the table scrollable.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FixedFooter
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When true, the footer will be visible is not scrolled to the bottom. Note: set Height to make the table scrollable.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Height
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Setting a height will allow to scroll the table. If not set, it will try to grow in height. You can set this to any CSS value that the
            attribute 'height' accepts, i.e. 500px. 
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SortLabel
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If table is in smalldevice mode and uses any kind of sorting the text applied here will be the sort selects label.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowUnsorted
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true allows table to be in an unsorted state through column clicks (i.e. first click sorts "Ascending", second "Descending", third "None").
            If false only "Ascending" and "Descending" states are allowed (i.e. there always should be a column to sort).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowsPerPage
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If the table has more items than this number, it will break the rows into pages of said size.
            Note: requires a MudTablePager in PagerContent.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CurrentPage
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The page index of the currently displayed page (Zero based). Usually called by MudTablePager.
            Note: requires a MudTablePager in PagerContent.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MultiSelection
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set to true to enable selection of multiple rows with check boxes. 
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ToolBarContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Optional. Add any kind of toolbar to this render fragment.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Loading
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Show a loading animation, if true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LoadingProgressColor
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The color of the loading progress if used. It supports the theme colors.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HeaderContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Add MudTh cells here to define the table header. If <see cref="P:MudBlazor.MudTableBase.CustomHeader" /> is set, add one or more MudTHeadRow instead.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CustomHeader
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specify if the header has multiple rows. In that case, you need to provide the MudTHeadRow tags.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HeaderClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Add a class to the thead tag
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FooterContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Add MudTd cells here to define the table footer. If<see cref="P:MudBlazor.MudTableBase.CustomFooter" /> is set, add one or more MudTFootRow instead.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CustomFooter
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specify if the footer has multiple rows. In that case, you need to provide the MudTFootRow tags.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FooterClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Add a class to the tfoot tag
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ColGroup
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a group of one or more columns in a table for formatting.
            Ex:
            table
                colgroup
                   col span="2" style="background-color:red"
                   col style="background-color:yellow"
                 colgroup
                 header
                 body
            table
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: PagerContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Add MudTablePager here to enable breaking the rows in to multiple pages.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ReadOnly

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Returns the item which was last clicked on in single selection mode (that is, if MultiSelection is false)
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItemChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Callback is called when a row has been clicked and returns the selected item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItems
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If MultiSelection is true, this returns the currently selected items. You can bind this property and the initial content of the HashSet you bind it to will cause these rows to be selected initially.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItemsChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Callback is called whenever items are selected or deselected in multi selection mode.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ServerData
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Supply an async function which (re)loads filtered, paginated and sorted data from server.
            Table will await this func and update based on the returned TableData.
            Used only with ServerData
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Elevation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The higher the number, the heavier the drop-shadow. 0 for no shadow.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Square
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set true to disable rounded corners
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Outlined
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true, table will be outlined.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Bordered
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true, table's cells will have left/right borders.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Dense
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set true for rows with a narrow height
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Hover
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set true to see rows hover on mouse-over.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Striped
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true, striped table rows will be used.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Breakpoint
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            At what breakpoint the table should switch to mobile layout. Takes None, Xs, Sm, Md, Lg and Xl the default behavior is breaking on Xs.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FixedHeader
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When true, the header will stay in place when the table is scrolled. Note: set Height to make the table scrollable.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FixedFooter
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When true, the footer will be visible is not scrolled to the bottom. Note: set Height to make the table scrollable.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Height
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Setting a height will allow to scroll the table. If not set, it will try to grow in height. You can set this to any CSS value that the
            attribute 'height' accepts, i.e. 500px. 
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SortLabel
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If table is in smalldevice mode and uses any kind of sorting the text applied here will be the sort selects label.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowUnsorted
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true allows table to be in an unsorted state through column clicks (i.e. first click sorts "Ascending", second "Descending", third "None").
            If false only "Ascending" and "Descending" states are allowed (i.e. there always should be a column to sort).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowsPerPage
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If the table has more items than this number, it will break the rows into pages of said size.
            Note: requires a MudTablePager in PagerContent.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CurrentPage
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The page index of the currently displayed page (Zero based). Usually called by MudTablePager.
            Note: requires a MudTablePager in PagerContent.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Validation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A validation func or a validation attribute. Supported types are:
            <para>Func<T, bool> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, string> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null </para>
            <para>Func<T, IEnumerable< string >> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< bool >> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task< string >> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null</para>
            <para>Func<T, Task<IEnumerable< string >>> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty</para>
            <para>System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.ValidationAttribute instances</para>
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" /> implementation targeting elements containing attributes with URL expected values.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Resolves URLs starting with '~/' (relative to the application's 'webroot' setting) that are not
            targeted by other <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" />s. Runs prior to other <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" />s to ensure
            application-relative URLs are resolved.</remarks>

<summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ValidationSummaryTagHelper
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" /> implementation targeting any HTML element with an <c>asp-validation-summary</c>
            attribute.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-validation-summary
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If <see cref="F:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ValidationSummary.All" /> or <see cref="F:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ValidationSummary.ModelOnly" />, appends a validation
            summary. Otherwise (<see cref="F:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ValidationSummary.None" />, the default), this tag helper does nothing.
            </summary>
            <exception cref="T:System.ArgumentException">
            Thrown if setter is called with an undefined <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ValidationSummaryTagHelper.ValidationSummary" /> value e.g.
            <c>(ValidationSummary)23</c>.
            </exception>

TagHelpers.Name: Bind
TagHelpers.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributes.Name: @bind-...
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: format
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies a format to convert the value specified by the corresponding bind attribute. For example: @bind-value:format="..." will apply a format string to the value specified in @bind-value="...". The format string can currently only be used with expressions of type DateTime.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: event
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the event handler name to attach for change notifications for the value provided by the '@bind-...' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: culture
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the culture to use for conversions.
